article.headline: UMBC 81, St. Peter's 78
article.story: CATONSVILLE, Md. (AP) -- Ray Barbosa scored 23 points and Maryland-Baltimore County erased a 10-point, second-half deficit, rallying for an 81-78 victory over St. Peter's on Saturday. Brian Hodges added 14 points and Darryl Proctor 11 for the Retrievers (1-0), who won for the first time in four meetings with the Peacocks (0-1). Raul Orta led St. Peter's with 19 points and Darrell Lampley scored 15. Nick Leon and Todd Sowell had 11 points each. Ryan Bacon's layup put the Peacocks ahead 59-49 with 10:44 left in the second half, but UMBC stiffened defensively, allowing only four field goals over the remainder of the game. The Retrievers put together an 11-4 run, taking their first lead, 69-68 on a putback by Hodges with 4:22 left. Orta's runner restored the St. Peter's lead, but Cavell Johnson put UMBC back on top with a turnarond jumper. With UMBC ahead 74-73, Bacon missed a dunk and Barbosa's baseline drive with 18.9 seconds to go put the Retrievers ahead by three points. Jay Greene, who had 10 assists, then intercepted Orta's pass, was fouled and hit a pair of free throws for a 78-73 edge with 7.7 seconds remaining. Orta had 16 first-half points and St. Peter's shot 17-for-29 from the field en route to a 43-36 lead at halftime.
